-- TABLE-Euro-zone M3 growth up in May, private loans contract
-- 
-- Mon Jun 30, 2014 04:18AM EDT
-- None



FRANKFURT, June 30 (Reuters) - Lending to households and firms in the euro zone contracted more sharply in May than a month earlier, while money supply growth picked up, the European Central Bank said on Monday.

The ECB gave the following percentage changes in growth,  seasonally adjusted: MAYAPRIL Prior   M3 annual growth rate   1.00.7   (0.8)  M3 3-month moving avg 12-mo growth  0.91.0   (1.0)   Annual total credit growth -2.3   -2.2  (-2.2)   Annual credit growth private sector-2.5   -2.5  (-2.5)-- of which loans -2.0   -1.8  (-1.8)   -- of which loans (adj. for sales   and securitisation)   -1.4   -1.6  (-1.5)  Breakdown of Loans, pct annual growth rate:   Loans to households-0.70.0   (0.0)-- consumer credit-2.2   -2.1  (-2.1)-- for home purchases -0.30.7   (0.7)   Loans to non-financial corporations-2.6   -2.8  (-2.8)  Loans to NFCs adj. for sales and   securitisation -2.5   -2.8  (-2.7)  Monthly loan flow to firms (bln euros)   -8 -6(-7)